  overview:
    "Cancer is the fourth sign of the zodiac, and it occupies a place of profound emotional depth, protective instinct, and primal nurturing power. Where the first three signs of the zodiac concern themselves with self-identity (Aries), material security (Taurus), and intellectual engagement (Gemini), Cancer turns the wheel inward toward the questions that haunt the human soul: Where do I belong? Who is my family? What does it mean to truly care for another person? Born at the height of the summer solstice, when the Sun reaches its zenith and begins its slow descent, Cancer carries the paradox of light and darkness within its very nature — the knowledge that peak abundance always carries the seed of eventual loss. This awareness is what makes Cancer so fiercely protective, so deeply sensitive, and so profoundly committed to creating safe harbors in an uncertain world. Ruled by the Moon, the celestial body that governs emotions, instincts, memory, and the unconscious, Cancer operates on a frequency that most other signs can barely perceive. They feel the room before they enter it. They sense tension before a word is spoken. They remember emotional nuances that others forgot months or even years ago. This is not sentimentality — it is a form of emotional intelligence so refined that it borders on the psychic. Cancer is cardinal water, which means they don't just feel — they act on their feelings. They are the ones who build homes, create families (biological or chosen), establish traditions, and weave the invisible web of care that holds communities together. Their energy is not passive or receptive in the way that water is often stereotyped — it is the energy of the tide, of the ocean current, of the river that carves canyons through sheer persistence. What you feel around a Cancer is something rare in this world: the sensation of being truly seen, truly remembered, and truly held.",

